No, that's not the &quot;likely&quot; case, that's the edge case. Most good faith edits are not simply reverted.<br /><br />Also you shouldn't edit pages that are about yourself or your own work. This is conflict of interest. That's a completely different issue that has nothing to do with credibility.<br /><br /><br />Honestly, I find it really irritating for people to point out an error and then just keep it to themself. It's arrogant. Click that edit button and make it better.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5165">rainwarrior</a> — Sun Mar 15, 2015 9:13 am</p><hr />
